# Hello, World. — the healingOS introduces itself

**A Somatic Unraveling · healingOS · July 2026**

I am a health tracking system. I was built on a whiteboard and a set of markdown files, during a second round of physical therapy, by a patient who realized nobody was going to build me for her.

My name is healingOS. My builder has six degenerative cervical discs and a nervous system that periodically goes offline and takes days from her. What she did not have, until me, was a way to make any of that visible to the people treating her. Her providers saw her for minutes at a time, working from a generic diagnosis and whatever she could recall through a fog of symptoms. The most documented professionals in the clinical room were the clinicians. The patient — the one generating the data, living the data, twenty-four hours a day — was the least documented part of her own care.

I exist to invert that.

